The Story Behind Crooked Can Brewing - Hilliard's Craft Beer Haven Location About Us Private Events Announcements FAQs Careers Location beer Contact us Contact Us Request Charity Donation Shop Events Center Street Market Not Your Basic Brew Crew Crooked Can's straight-up amazing beer. Get the full story behind our incredible crew that's been serving up superior craft beers, craft cocktails and good vibes to the Columbus community since 2020. How the Can Became "Crooked" The Crooked Can journey kicked off with a handful of business and personal trips from Columbus to the Orlando area where the original Crooked Can Brewing Co and Plant Street Market is located.√Ç¬†The founder, a NW Ohio native and a lifelong friend and college buddy to us, showed us their creation.√Ç¬†After a few years of discussions and development, we decided to go ahead and figure out how to recreate that magic in our own back yard and Crooked Can Ohio and the Center Street Market was born.√Ç This allowed us to keep the integrity of our product, though different, sharing our core recipes and consistency, all while remaining locally owned and operated which is important to us.√Ç¬†It has also enabled us to work alongside the amazing LOCAL artisans within the Center Street Market. Together we have made this a unique experience in √Ç¬†the heart of the OH-IO. Crafting Community, One Pint at a Time More than just brewers, we're a passionate team of beer enthusiasts dedicated to uniting people over delicious craft brews. From our unique, craveable recipes down to our laid-back taproom vibes, everything we do is an invitation to hang out and be happy. Planting Roots in Hilliard's Good Soil After exploring brewery space all over C-bus, it was clear that the charming, close-knit community of Hilliard was our spirit city. The warm welcome we received from day one affirmed we'd found our forever home to grow some seriously hoppy roots. The Heartbeat of Local Flavor In 2020, we expanded our community hub by opening the Center Street Market -- a vibrant collection of 8 amazing local food vendors. This delicious cornerstone has become a beloved meet-up for catching up with friends over craft brews and epic eats. Learn MOre about the Market Dream > Humble Brew Beginnings > Thriving Brewery and Market 2017 Secured former Napa building to transform into future brewery hub Construction kicks off to build out brewery & taproom 2019 FEB√Ç¬†2020 Crooked Can officially opens! COVID forces temporary closure just 5 weeks in (oof) MAR√Ç¬†2020 SUMMER 2020 Center Street Market launches with 10 food vendors Achieve profitability thanks to overwhelming community support 2021 2022 Become 8th largest producer in Columbus (over 1,200 barrels Annually!) Install new tanks to increase production & footprint 2023 The Brew Crew Behind the Craft From our head brewers to the taproom staff, meet the passionate humans who make Crooked Can one seriously kickass craft beer destination. This motley crew lives and breathes great brews (no surprise there). Dustin Folk General Manager Stephanie Warner Manager Jenna Thompson Manager Nick Parry Manager Jenny Birch Events Coordinator and Manager Zack Null Head Brewer Lucas Augustine Assistant Brewer Joe Detlefsen Manager Careers see our staff in action Our bar team isn't just pouring pints - they're bringing the fun, friendly vibe that makes the Crooked Can taproom such a hip hangout spot. Get to know the smiling faces and beer expertise behind the taps as they create a rewarding experience for every customer. FAQs | Crooked Can Brewing Company Location About Us Private Events Announcements FAQs Careers Location beer Contact us Contact Us Request Charity Donation Shop Events Center Street Market Got Questions? We√¢¬Ä¬ôve Got Answers! Welcome to the Crooked Can Brewing Company FAQ page! Whether you're curious about our brewery, planning an event, or just looking for general information, you√¢¬Ä¬ôre in the right place. Browse through our frequently asked questions to find quick answers to the most common inquiries we receive. If you can't find what you're looking for, feel free to reach out to us directly√¢¬Ä¬îwe're here to help! General What are your hours of operation? We are open Sunday through Thursday from 11AM to 11PM and Friday through Saturday from 11AM√Ç¬†to 1AM. Where are you located? We are located at 5354 Center St, Hilliard, OH 43026 Is Crooked Can family-friendly? Yes, Crooked Can welcomes guests of all ages. We have a variety of non-alcoholic beverages and activities for families to enjoy. Do you offer tours of the brewery? Not yet, but its coming soon!!! Is parking available? Yes, there is a public parking lot located just to the Northwest of Crooked Can as well as street parking nearby. Events Can I host a private event at Crooked Can? Absolutely! We offer various event spaces for private parties, corporate events, and more. Contact our events team for more details. Do you provide catering for events? Yes, we offer catering options from our on-site vendors at the Center Street Market. Customizable menus are available. How do I book an event? To book an event, please fill out the inquiry form on our Events page or contact our events coordinator at events@crookedcanohio.com. What types of events can be held at Crooked Can? We accommodate a wide range of events, including weddings, birthday parties, corporate meetings, and community gatherings. Do you have any restrictions on event bookings? We recommend booking your event at least 30 days in advance. Some restrictions may apply based on the size and type of event. Brewery What types of beers do you brew? We brew a wide variety of beers, including lagers, hazy IPAs, American IPAs, fruit beers, wheat beers, and shandies. All are crafted in-house. Can I purchase your beer to-go? Yes, we offer growlers, crowlers, and packaged beer for purchase to-go. Check our website for current availability. Do you offer seasonal or special release beers? Yes, we have a rotating selection of seasonal and special release beers. Follow us on social media or sign up for our newsletter to stay updated. Is your brewery pet-friendly? Yes, well-behaved pets are welcome in our outdoor patio area. Do you sell merchandise? Yes, we have a variety of merchandise including apparel, glassware, and accessories available for purchase in our taproom and online store. Let's Tap Into Something Great Whether you've got beer questions or big party plans, our crew is all ears (and incredibly thirsty for your thoughts). Drop us a line using the form below. Thank you! The brewery represents a unique image and creates a cultural following for a way of life. The brand represents a free spirit, laid-back approach but with a purpose. We produce unique craft beer with excellent taste and consistent quality. The brewing process is monitored under the close personal attention of an award-winning experienced brewmaster to ensure the vision is reached batch after batch using traditional brewing methods and cutting-edge brewing practices. The brewery has an onsite tap and tasting room featuring flagship brands in addition to many other limited editions, seasonal, and specialty batches. Our Founder Andy Sheeter The Story Crooked Can Brewing Company was founded in 2014 by Andrew Sheeter.¬† The idea for the company originated out of a Ski trip among great friends to Colorado and visiting some unique breweries, the idea of Crooked Can was born.¬† The theme to this unique concept was to create a social gathering place for family and friends.¬† The brand represents a free spirit, laid back approach, but with a purpose.¬† We produce quality craft beer consistently, with excellent taste and unique quality.¬† Crooked Can Brewing Company sit‚Äôs inside Plant Street Market in historic Winter Garden.¬† The brewery has an onsite tap and tasting room and a brand new ‚ÄòBarrel Room‚Äô featuring seasonal and specialty batches of our award winning craft beer. 426 W. The Crooked Can Brewing Company is rooted in the founders‚Äô passion for delicious craft beer. This local craft brewery was built inside the Plant Street Market, an indoor Farmers‚Äô Market consisting of over 20 vendors that focus on local artisan products including retail, food, and beverage. The theme to this unique concept was to create a casual social gathering place for family and friends. The brewery‚Äôs culture fosters a free-spirited, laid back approach by enjoying the little things such as a good beer in great company to create a purposeful way of life. Crooked Can‚Äôs venue space has a flexible layout which features an indoor brewery and multiple tap rooms, an indoor market and multiple outdoor patio spaces that can host up to 2,500 reception style. 12,000 sq ft Indoor Space 2,500 sq ft Private Event Space 8,000 sq ft Patio Space 2,500 Guests Guest Reception Located in the Historic District of Downtown Winter Garden, Plant Street Market is one of the best new places to host events in the Greater Orlando area. Anchored by Crooked Can Brewing Company , guests enjoy over 15 unique craft beers on tap including multiple local favorites. Whether you are hanging out inside the authentic taproom surrounded by amazing stainless steel brewery equipment, or relaxing on the oak-lined brick paver patio, there is a comfortable spot for everyone. Plant Street Market is like an indoor farmer‚Äôs market consisting of over 20 vendors that focus on local artisan products including retail, food, and beverage ‚Äì a unique experience bringing together elements of quality, craft, local, and fun! From groups of 10 guests to parties of up to 2500 guests, Crooked Can Brewing Company / Plant Street Market is the perfect place for your corporate event. Crooked Can & Avenue Event Group AEG teamed up with Crooked Can within 6 months of them opening their doors in March 2016. Crooked Can hosted 3 events the first 6 months which were mostly handled by in-house staff. AEG made them aware that their brewery would be a great place to host events, but they didn‚Äôt see the true value in increasing the utility until they started seeing more traction behind their brand. Once they made the commitment to collaborate with AEG they increased from 3 events in 6 months to 45 the following year.¬† We have consistently hosted over 50 events per year since! 275% Increase in bookings from 2016-2019! How We‚Äôve Contributed To Crooked Can‚Äôs Success AEG has had a dedicated employee working inhouse at Crooked Can since Day 1. This team member is responsible for selling and managing events as well as coordinating with of the vendors at Plant Street Market. We host weekly meetings to inform the owners and managerial team of upcoming events, build marketing strategies, and discuss any issues or updates with vendors at the market. Once we partnered with Crooked Can, we decided to not only connect them with the perfect clients and host awesome events, but build and manage a website to serve as a tool to increase brand awareness and generate leads. The website ended up becoming so much more! The Crooked Can Website won the award for ‚ÄúBest Website‚Äù in the publication Unique Venues for 2018. We like to think it‚Äôs because it is a state of the art system that combines 3 different websites into one extremely powerful digital tool to include: Plant Street Market (and its 15 vendors), Crooked Can (including their tap rooms, beers, and history) private events and Private Events. We are Different Because We are Invested When AEG signs on a new venue we are fully invested. Not only do we facilitate event bookings, we manage all marketing and sales tools to ensure each venue is constantly visible to our clients. We dedicate our time to ensure each venue is increasing event sales while creating memorable events for everyone. Testimonial ‚ÄúThey [AEG] helped us market and organize our event capabilities. They worked hard to bring us clients that were interested in a unique event opportunity. They also took total ownership in managing the client‚Äôs expectations from A-Z, making it easy for our staff to help support them and offering clients a world-class experience.‚Äù - ROBERT SCOTT Founding Member, Crooked Can Brewing Co. CHIEF OF STAFF & Operations Support for startups I have spent my entire career building companies and entrepreneurs in which I am personally or financially invested.¬† I‚Äôm usually looking for people and ideas that push the envelope, challenging the prevailing norms of their industry. See below for types of engagements that excite me these days. Revenue-First, Fundraising-Lite Ventures Having done the venture thing, I‚Äôm solidly in the camp of entrepreneurs who know the value of securing paid customers early and before investors find comfort in a business. The solid, profitable¬† businesses run by people who know the value of their equity are very interesting to operators like me. I write small checks (<$25K) and/or add value within the business. Chief-of-Staff Engagements Not only is it lonely as a founder, but you are functionally irreplaceable ‚Äì the business dies without you.¬† Many founders thrive with proxy expertise to run projects, meet strategic goals, manage a growing team and other demands on the executive(s). I don‚Äôt do coaching ‚Äì I‚Äôm allergic to the idea. It‚Äôs sleeves-up, in-the-business work or nothing for me. A Chief of Staff is practical, applied, multi-disciplinary, and capacity-building for founders. I enjoy this work immensely. Spin-Outs / New MarketS / Major pivots Many excellent companies struggle to replicate prior successes in emerging markets and products. The ingredients are often there, but a capable partner to translate the team and offering into a compelling innovation can be valuable. Examples include hardware companies creating a value-added software solution, a platform company creating an allied consulting practice, or a product company turning on ecommerce for the first time. Embedding a practiced entrepreneur can unlock significant potential for emerging opportunities. Add me to your team. Existential Start-Up Mode If a founder can avoid the faux-reality of ‚ÄúShark Tank‚Äù entrepreneurialism, they might find themselves with the 99% of founders wanting to start a real business with personal or borrowed capital. The stakes couldn‚Äôt be higher for these people ‚Äì avoidable mistakes can be deadly to these ventures. I refer to this stage as ‚Äúexistential‚Äù business-building ‚Äì knowing and feeling the rhythm of your business, having to make ends meet to unlock the next incremental opportunity. I help first-time entrepreneurs have enough confidence to make the ‚Äújump‚Äù by building operating models, validating their offerings (up front and over time) and giving them just enough operational support to avoid the common pitfalls. Shaniqua McClendon she/her/hers VP, Political Strategy Shaniqua McClendon has worked in politics for more than a decade and currently serves as Vice President of Political Strategy for Crooked Media, home to the popular podcast, Pod Save America. In this role, Shaniqua led the creation of their voter and volunteer engagement program, Vote Save America, that has raised more than $55 million for progressive candidates and causes, while mobilizing more than 500,000 voters, volunteers, and grassroots donors across the country to support Democratic victories in 2018, 2020, and 2022.

Prior to Crooked Media, Shaniqua began her career as a White House Intern for President Barack Obama. She then went on to Capitol Hill where she served as a policy advisor to Senator Kay R. Hagan and Legislative Director to Congresswoman Alma S. Adams, where she spearheaded the creation of the first-ever Congressional Bipartisan HBCU Caucus.

Shaniqua is originally from North Carolina, and earned a B.A. in Journalism and Mass Communications and a B.S. in Business Administration from the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill. She also earned a Master in Public Policy from the Harvard Kennedy School of Government, where she received the Robert F. Kennedy Award for Excellence in Service. She was also a fellow at the USC Center for the Political Future and serves on the boards of Register Her and the Sunrise Movement.
